    <md:abstract>This course deals with signals, systems, and transforms, from
      their theoretical mathematical foundations to practical implementation in
      circuits and computer algorithms. At the conclusion of ELEC 301, you
      should have a deep understanding of the mathematics and practical issues
      of signals in continuous and discrete time, linear time invariant systems,
      convolution, and Fourier transforms.
    </md:abstract>

